(Index.html):
Home Page
Serves as the entry point to the application.
Introduces the system, its purpose, and provides navigation to the data input form.
Highlights the project goal: Predicting chronic disease risks through AI-powered analysis.
Includes links to:
Form Page (for submitting user data)
Dashboard Page (for viewing results)

Allows users to enter their personal, lifestyle, and health-related details through a structured form.
Fields include:
Demographics: Age, Gender, Height, Weight, BMI, Region
Lifestyle: Smoking Status, Alcohol Consumption, Physical Activity, Diet Quality, Sleep Hours, Stress Level
Health Metrics: Blood Pressure (Sys/Dia), Cholesterol, Glucose, Family History, Existing Conditions
Once submitted, the data is sent as a JSON object via HTTP POST request to the API Gateway endpoint using JavaScript’s fetch() API.
Includes basic validation (e.g., empty field checks, numerical input validation).

(Dasboard.html)
Results and Visualization
Displays the predicted disease risk score retrieved from the backend through a GET request.
Shows:
Risk Score (0–100)
Risk Level: Low, Moderate, or High (color-coded)
Health Recommendations: lifestyle adjustments, preventive actions, or consultation advice
Implements dynamic data rendering using JavaScript and Bootstrap progress bars or charts to visualize risk levels.
